<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-05T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-05T03:00:00-05:00" n="761" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d761">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.48g/81: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-05T16:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            5, 1921—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 5—10
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>4. Your 400, December 29, 3 p.m. Conditions of all Legations must be
                                met before surtax can be levied. Entire matter still under
                                consideration. Date [of] beginning of tax not yet certain.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>